sic experience, Huawei and Kfm took to the streets with the #HuaweiKDay bus and travelled through the city offering fans the opportunity to win tickets, engage with their favourite presenters and meet artists featured on the Huawei KDay line-up. The #HuaweiKDay tour bus visited key locales in the city including: Location Start: Kfm Radio – Somerset Road Greenpoint LighthouseCafé Caprice Newlands poolsBP Wetton RoadTotal Viking Road Tygervalley Shopping Centre End: The Square at Century City“Huawei KDay is the perfect fusion of music, lifestyle and technology. The event is in its twelfth year and continues to draw more than 15,000 Capetonians to Meerendal Estate for the Cape’s premier music experience,” said Kfm 94.5 Programming Manager, Stephen Werner. Werner added: “To launch the opening of ticket sales we journeyed through the city with the ultimate music tour, giving away tickets and celebrating the event with listeners. We ended off the day with a special Huawei KDay performance by Goodluck and Majozi. #HuaweiKDay fans can expect further exciting promotional activity from us over the coming months.” “Huawei Kday is a representation of Huawei’s vision of connecting people, through innovative technology and unrivalled experiences. We are extremely proud to partner with Kfm 94.5 to bring more than 15,000 people together, through the universal language of music. Look forward to the ultimate music spectacle at Huawei KDay 2019,” said Akhram Mohamed, CTO Huawei Consumer Business Group South Africa. Event-goers can look forward to experiencing Mi Casa, Goodluck, Craig Lucas, Kurt Darren, Lady Zamar, Youngsta CPT, The Kiffness, DJ Kent, Majozi, Pascal & Pearce ft. Jethro Tait, Doctor Victor and the Rasta Rebels, Timo ODV, Jamali and Chad Saaiman. Tickets are priced from R300 for adults while children under the age of 12 will pay R150. Tickets for the Chill Zone are priced at R490 and are available through Computicket. Stay tuned to Kfm 94.5 and www.kfm.co.za for additional line-up updates and other Huawei KDay 2019 news. Engage via social media using #HuaweiKDay, @HuaweiZA and @Kfmza. Event details: Event: Huawei KDay 2019 with Kfm 94.5 Date: Saturday, 2 March 2019Time: 11am – 8pmVenue: Meerendal Wine Estate, DurbanvilleTickets are available through Computicket:  R300 adults  R150 for children under 12  R490 Kfm Chill Zone Social media hashtag: #HuaweiKDay